#| -- Scan the table "tbl_name" from the SQLite file "test.db"
#| SELECT * FROM sqlite_scan('⟨test.db⟩', '⟨tbl_name⟩');

# DOCS_TEST_BODY

query error
SELECT * FROM sqlite_scan('test.db', 'tbl_name');
----
db error: ERROR: Table Function with name "sqlite_scan" is not in the catalog, but it exists in the sqlite_scanner extension.

This feature relies on the "sqlite_scanner" extension which is not built into this SereneDB binary. Please open an issue at https://github.com/serenedb/serenedb/issues if you need it.


